ce:section.ce:para:
The synthesis of KCD followed a specific procedure. CDs were prepared using a hydrothermal method from CA and EDA [15]. As depicted in Scheme 1
                        , a specified amount of CDs was dispersed in deionized water, while KH550 was dissolved in anhydrous ethanol (the precise formulation is detailed in Table 1
                        ). The mixture was stirred for 30 min at 25 °C and then stirred for an additional 5 h in a water bath at 60 °C, both at 200 r/min. After cooling to room temperature, the dispersion was centrifuged at 12,000 r/min for 15 min to collect the precipitate, which was then washed three times with anhydrous ethanol to eliminate unreacted raw materials. The resulting product was placed in an oven at 60 °C and dried for 12 h. Consequently, a series of KCDs with varying mass ratios were prepared. For instance, based on the different mass ratios of CDs-to-KH550, the prepared KCDs were designated as 1:1-KCD, 1:3-KCD, 1:5-KCD, etc., as shown in Table 1.
